$${N_{{\rm<Subscript></Subscript>}}} = {A_{\rm{D}}}{\left[ {{{{\rm{MAT}}} \over {2\pi {\rm{C}}{{\rm{V}}^2}t3}}} \right]^{1/2}}\exp \left( { - {{{{(t - {\rm{MAT}})}^2}} \over {2{\rm{C}}{{\rm{V}}^2}{\rm{MAT}}t}}} \right)$$
\end{document}. The above-derived equation is similar to the IG function and corresponds to Eq. (3) in Weiss (1996). Further, mathematical properties of Eq. (24) are discussed by Weiss (1996), Ring (2001), and Ring et al. (2000).

The PK model that was used to describe the data is a 1-compartment massbalance model with first-order elimination:
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
